# Bash Commands for Meeting Design Lab

## Project Navigation

### Quick Overview
```bash
# Show project structure (3 levels, no clutter)
tree -I 'node_modules|.git|coverage|dist|build|.next|out' -L 3 --dirsfirst
```

### Find Slider Components
```bash
# Find all slider-related files
find . -name "*[Ss]lider*" -type f | grep -v node_modules

# Search for slider implementations in code
grep -r "Slider" --include="*.jsx" --include="*.tsx" --exclude-dir=node_modules .
```

### Find Meeting Design Lab Components
```bash
# Find Team Intro and Meeting components
find . \( -name "*[Tt]eam*" -o -name "*[Ii]ntro*" -o -name "*[Mm]eeting*" \) \
  -type f \( -name "*.jsx" -o -name "*.tsx" \) | grep -v node_modules
```

### Search for Specific Code
```bash
# Find files containing attendees or salary sliders
grep -r -l "attendees\|salary" --include="*.jsx" --include="*.tsx" --exclude-dir=node_modules .
```

## Component Structure

### View Components Only
```bash
# Show only React component files
tree -P '*.jsx|*.tsx' --prune -I 'node_modules|coverage|dist|build'
```

### View Styles Only
```bash
# Show only CSS/style files
tree -P '*.css|*.scss|*.module.css' --prune -I 'node_modules'
```

## Development Shortcuts

### Quick Component Search
```bash
# Search for a specific component by name
find . -name "*ComponentName*" | grep -E "\.(jsx?|tsx?)$" | grep -v node_modules
```

### Find TODO Comments
```bash
# Find all TODO comments in the codebase
grep -r "TODO\|FIXME" --include="*.jsx" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.js" --exclude-dir=node_modules .
```

## Git Helpers

### Show Changed Files
```bash
# Show files changed in the last commit
git diff --name-only HEAD~1 HEAD

# See what files have changed
git status

# See the commit history
git log --oneline -10

# Show files with "slider" that were recently modified
git log --name-only --pretty=format: | grep -i slider | sort -u
```

## Running These Commands

1. Copy the command you need
2. Paste in your terminal
3. Run from the project root directory

## Tips

- Add `-v node_modules` to most `find` commands to exclude node_modules
- Use `| head -20` to limit output to first 20 results
- Add `| wc -l` to count results instead of listing them
- Use `pbcopy` (Mac) or `xclip` (Linux) to copy output to clipboard

## Project-Specific Paths

Based on our project structure, key directories to check:
- `src/components/` - React components
- `src/styles/` or `styles/` - Global styles
- `app/` - Next.js app directory (if using App Router)
- `pages/` - Next.js pages (if using Pages Router)
